How to Create and Use a Python Virtual Environment?

Create a Virtual Environment:

python -m venv myenv
myenv is the name of the virtual environment folder.

Activate the Virtual Environment:

On Windows:
myenv\Scripts\activate

On Mac/Linux:
source myenv/bin/activate

Install Packages Inside the Virtual Environment:
pip install package_name

Deactivate the Virtual Environment:
deactivate

Delete a Virtual Environment:

Simply delete the myenv folder:
rm -rf myenv

Common Use Cases

Working on multiple projects with conflicting dependencies.
Sharing the exact development environment with others (using requirements.txt).
Testing libraries or tools without affecting the global Python setup.